        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Wolfgang.Etl.Abstractions.EtlPipelineSourceExtensions",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Wolfgang.Etl.Abstractions.EtlPipelineSourceExtensions.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Built-in source factories for <xref href=\"Wolfgang.Etl.Abstractions.EtlPipeline\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>. They begin a pipeline from a raw stream or\nan extractor. Format packages add their own class-named source factories (for example\n<code>CsvExtractor</code>) as extension methods on <xref href=\"Wolfgang.Etl.Abstractions.EtlPipeline\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> alongside these, so every\nsource reads the same way: <code>EtlPipeline.Create().Xxx(...)</code>.</p>\n"
    },
